properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 10 at 3:41PM HST until February 11 at 6:00PM HST by NWS Honolulu HI
properties.description:
* WHAT...North to northwest winds 15 to 25 kt and seas 12 to 20
feet.

* WHERE...Kauai Northwest Waters, Kauai Windward Waters, Kauai
Leeward Waters, Kauai Channel, Oahu Windward Waters, Oahu
Leeward Waters, Alenuihaha Channel, Big Island Windward Waters
and Big Island Southeast Waters.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM HST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
A Small Craft Advisory means that wind speeds of 25 to 33 knots
and/or seas 10 feet or greater are expected to produce conditions
hazardous to small craft. Inexperienced mariners, especially
those operating smaller vessels, should avoid navigating in these
conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM HST TUESDAY... ...GALE WARNING IS CANCELLED
